:: Experimentation3 {"position":"1425,1250","size":"100,100"}
Most of the focus that night was spent futzing about with reckoning tiny changes, like the weight of a single feather, or changing the exact color of ink. The former was aimless experimentation, possibly a hope of figuring out a new material for spellcraft -- the latter was a convenience that she had messed around with too much. 

Now, there was a bottle-shaped hole *in her desk*. Not exactly sure how *that* happened.  {reveal link:"And what's more...", passage:"Experimentation4"}


:: Experimentation4 {"position":"1525,1250","size":"100,100"}
She remembered taking up an old book, one which came from the Ranch itself to be sure, from the bedside table, and reckoning into existence that she had read the entire thing, like she was a schoolchild trying to cram before a book report -- and the whole thing, cover to cover, became utterly blank, its knowledge moved from page to mind wholecloth. Not even the title of the book remained.  Purely cut-and-paste... 

The binding broke, blank paper spilled out over the room, across stain of wine and glass and wood. The knowledge she'd tried to reality-bend into herself... well, that was a forgone haze...



