The scarecrows signalled the changing winds like flag-bearers... Her riding-boots clanked, the spurs resonating with the bustle of the festival outside. She could hear everything in a square mile, and she could harmonize with it... 

The wind and rain and sun were flowing through her as one. The plains and her were ONE. 

<`What's happening?`> The Witch heard {herName}'s alarmed thoughts from across the room, as her eyes darted this-way-and-that. <`It's all so... captivating... so pretty...`>

It won't be for much longer.

The witch's feet breach the dirt at water's edge, on the precipice of a lake of stars... shadow gathered around her as her bare hands collect star after star... she close her eyes to its whisper. When the Witch opens her eyes again, her vision fills with only red, and {herName}. 

The words are effortless; the foundations of the rickety old fort quaking like a colossal earthquake.

The witch's temper erupts, and her Gift cascades into an explosion of color, from her head to her heart and then through her mouth...

>[[~~USE THE CURSE.~~->Jogues.Hanna.Cursed1]]


