[align center]
**"As the Witch of the Plains, sure as the star falls and the years turn, I curse you so that no man will love you -- *ever again*!"**
[after 5 seconds]

The temperature plummets several degrees. The curse seems to slice apart the very space between them, and the witch spat the phrase like she'd spoken them a million times: which, for all intents, she had. A lonely teardrop falls into the lake of stars. *Her* sorrow was *sown*. 

Reality swayed underneath her. The tremendous weight of her soul, verdant and evanescent, coursed from the tip of her wand and seized upon Hanna in a moment, flooding her very heart with so much energy. 

{herName}'s fate was engraved with this truth-from-fiction. No more love. No more happiest day. 

~~PERFECT VICTORY.~~

All the air shunted itself out of the fort in a violent instant, and as it coursed back in and repressurized, their ears pop harder than they ever had... 

But the witch held her ground... 

